If you are viewing this story via our mobile app and are unable to see videos and tweets, click here. Goals by Victor Hedman in the closing seconds of the first period and Corey Perry in the early minutes of the second sparked the Lightning to a 5-3 victory over the Maple Leafs in Game 2 of their first-round playoff series Wednesday at Scotiabank Arena in Toronto. Tampa Bay tied the best-of-seven series at one game apiece heading to Game 3 Friday at Amalie Arena. Hedman scored a power-play goal with 2.5 seconds left in the opening period, then hit Perry with a stretch pass that Perry turned into a breakaway goal just over two minutes into the second. The Leafs got on the board with just over eight minutes remaining in the second after Auston Matthews forced a Ryan McDonagh turnover and Mitch Marner set up Michael Bunting for a one-timer. The Lightning got the goal right back on a Nikita Kucherov power-play goal after Wayne Simmons took a bad post-whistle penalty for roughing. Tampa Bay’s Brandon Hagel and Brayden Point, and Toronto’s Mitch Marner and Alex Kerfoot closed out the scoring in the third period. Here’s how it happened: Third period Auston Matthews shot off the rush saved by Vasilevskiy LIGHTNING GOAL: Nick Paul breaks up give-and-go play, and Brandon Hagel scores at the other end. Lightning 4, Maple Leafs 1. William Nylander penalized for tripping Bellemare, and the Lightning go on the power play leading by three goals Wayne Simmonds penalized for cross-checking Perry, who appears to have hurt his left arm LIGHTNING GOAL: Brayden Point scores off feed from Nikita Kucherov on the power play. Lightning 5, Leafs 1. MAPLE LEAFS GOAL: Mitch Marner scores, with Auston Matthews on the doorstep. Lightning 5, Leafs 2. MAPLE LEAFS GOAL: Alex Kerfoot scores shorthanded. Lightning 5, Leafs 3. Brayden Point penalized after pulling down Auston Matthews, putting Toronto on the power play with 2-1/2 minutes remaining Nylander blast from the left circle goes behind the ne